race.comment: LADY ZAYDI (10) is a consistent mare who must be close to another win. Raced on the pace and battled on well for a close second over 1200m here three weeks ago. New to this trip but it should not be a concern. Maps nicely just off the leading pair and this might be her race. TOO MANY THOUGHTS (5) stalked the leader and was a shade too good for LADY ZAYDI when resuming over 1200m here last start. Lightly raced gelding who is in for a big campaign so is worth following. THE BOSS MAN (13) led and looked the winner but was nailed late over 1350m at Ipswich recently. Should be peaking at the third run back from a spell. Just needs luck from the wide gate. KNOWITALL FRANK (16) returned from a spell with a win here in a non-tab race on Melbourne Cup Day. Up in grade but cannot be ruled out. NORTH COURT (4) drops in class on his first-up run. Fitter and looks to get in very well after the claim.
